title: Drawing, "Recto: Study: Maidenhair Fern, Trumpet-Vine, Nasturtium / Verso: Studies: Roses, Hollyhock, Elm", early 20th century
inscribed: recto: S. L. Crownfield (inscribed by her sister, Gertrude) / No. 7
creditline: Gift of Starling W. Childs and Ward Cheney
description: Vertical sheet depicting studies of maidenhair fern, trumpet-vine and nasturtium naturalistically rendered. On the verso, studies of roses, hollyhock leaves and elm trees
